        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>Since we expect the mm emission to be synchrotron radiaiton from a jet, we do not expect spectral lines, so request a simple pseudio-continuum setup. </prj:justificationText>
            <prj:justificationKey>ED_CORRELATOR</prj:justificationKey>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>We do not expect to resolve our target at the requested frequency (the source is likley associated with a milliarcsec-scale structure). </prj:justificationText>
            <prj:justificationKey>ED_ANGULAR_RESOLUTION</prj:justificationKey>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>The requested sensitivity (5 microJy at 100 GHz) will be sufficient to detect A0620-00 at the 4-sigma level if it were a flat spectrum 20 microJy source, as detected at 5.25 GHz by the VLA in 2013. </prj:justificationText>
            <prj:justificationKey>ED_SENSITIVITY</prj:justificationKey>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
